Sentencas: Conventional (La, Sr)MnO3 (LSM) electrodes modified by ion impregnation methods showed promising potential as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After impregnation of ionic conducting- type Gd0.2Ce0.8(NO3)(x) nitrite salt solution into the LSM structure, electrochemical activity of LSM electrodes for the O-2 reduction reaction was substantially enhanced.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700degreesC, the electrode polarization resistance of impregnated LSM electrodes decreased to 0.72 Omega cm(2) as compared to 26.4 Omega cm(2) for pure LSM electrodes, a reduction in electrode polarization resistance by 36 times.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization losses were also reduced substantially.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 300 mA cm(-2) and 700degreesC, overpotential for the O-2 reduction was reduced from 0.79 V on pure LSM to 0.19 V on impregnated LSM electrodes, a reduction in overpotential by four times.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ion-impregnated LSM electrodes showed better performance than those of LSM/Y2O3-ZrO2 and LSM/(Gd,Ce)O-2 composite electrodes as reported in the literature.
Titulo: Development of (La, Sr)MnO3-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
